name: AVURLAsset
desc: A concrete subclass of AVAsset that's used to initialize an asset from a local or remote URL.

items.name: url
items.desc: The URL with which the asset was initialized.

items.name: resourceLoader
items.desc: The resource loader associated with the asset.

items.name: compatibleTrack
items.desc: Returns an asset track from which any time range can be inserted into a given composition track.

items.name: audiovisualMIMETypes
items.desc: Returns an array of the MIME types the AVURLAsset class supports.

items.name: audiovisualTypes
items.desc: Returns an array of the file types the AVURLAsset class supports.

items.name: isPlayableExtendedMIMEType
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether the asset is playable with the given codec(s) and container type.

items.name: assetCache
items.desc: The assetâ€™s associated asset cache, if it exists.

items.name: mayRequireContentKeysForMediaDataProcessing
items.desc: Allows a URL asset to be added as a content key recipient to a content key session.

items.name: response
items.desc: The URL response for the loading request.
